    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-13T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-13T04:00:00-05:00" n="879"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d879">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/193: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-13T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >April 13, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 13—9:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Embassy’s 76, April 8, 6 p.m.<note n="89" xml:id="d879fn89">Not
                        printed.</note> transmitting a message for Standard-Vacuum.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The oil conversations ended today and the special representatives of the
                        oil interests are leaving Japan in the near future to consult with their
                        home offices.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Faced with the danger of a definite break with the large oil interests,
                        the Japanese officials today gave the special representatives last minute
                        promises of future fulfillment of practically all the desiderata of the
                        foreign oil interests. This fact cannot however be published either in Japan
                        or abroad for fear of ultra patriotic reaction which might defeat the plans
                        of the authorities to ameliorate the requirements of the law. Details of the
                            understanding<note n="90" xml:id="d879fn90">For text, see <hi
                                rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note> reached will be transmitted on the
                        15th to Standard-Vacuum New York through the Department.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
